- 1.12.0
    - **JSONB Field Discovery** — see what's inside your JSONB columns
        - `GetTableDetail` now returns full JSONB key metadata: field name, value type (string/number/boolean/object/array), and up to 3 sample values
        - Fixed: `discoverJSONBKeys` was stripping value_type and sample_vals, only returned key names — now returns complete `JSONBKeyInfo` structs
        - Frontend table detail page shows JSONB fields in a structured table (field name, type tag, sample values) instead of plain tag list
    - **Data Catalog Performance & Bug Fixes**
        - Fix: `GetDataDictionary` now caches results for 10 minutes — previously every request triggered N×4 SQL queries (columns/indexes/enums/time-range) against all tables
        - Fix: `discoverEnumValues` now skips 20+ known high-cardinality columns (name, symbol, description, etc.) — previously queried every text column in every table
        - Fix: `SafeIdentifierRe` no longer allows dots in SQL identifiers — defense-in-depth against injection via `schema.table` patterns
        - Fix: `ListTables` returns `[]` instead of JSON `null` when domain filter matches nothing
        - Fix: `GetTableDetail` controller returns 500 for internal errors (was returning 404 for all errors)
        - Fix: Cache update race condition in `getTables` — `cacheTime` now set before `cachedTables`
    - **Date Normalization**
        - Fix: `normalizeDateYYYYMMDD` in Go now handles `YYYYMMDD` format (e.g. `"20260507"` → `"2026-05-07"`)
    - **Test Fixes**
        - Fix: `taxonomy_controller_test` nil pointer dereference on `ParentCode` — JSON `null` → `*string` nil check
        - Fix: `catalog_dao_test` referenced unexported `safeIdentifierRe` → `SafeIdentifierRe`
        - Fix: `corporate_action_controller_test` and `financial_statement_controller_test` — `DataJSON` type mismatch (`string` → `json.RawMessage`) + double-encoded JSON handling
    - **Migration SQL**
        - New: `migrations/postgresql/security/0005_security_registry.sql` — security registry table on `pg_default`
